OL,7,FA pensioner supplied vulnerable young
OL,8,Fwomen with heroin in exchange for them
OL,9,Fworking as prostitutes as part of a
OL,10,F"catalogue of offending", a court has
OL,11,Fheard.
OL,13,FBelfast Crown Court was told Oliver
OL,14,FJames MacCormack is now facing a
OL,15,Fsubstantial jail sentence.
OL,17,FMacCormack, 71, whose address was
OL,18,Fgiven as Maghaberry Prison, has
OL,19,Fpleaded guilty to 40 offences which
OL,20,Finclude charges of human trafficking
OL,21,Fand controlling prostitution.
